OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774004767
OL,3,CKing dons sturdy shoes on trek to mark
OL,4,Claunch of coastal path and nature
OL,5,Creserve
OL,7,FThe King donned his sturdy shoes as he
OL,8,Fmarked the opening of England's newest
OL,9,Fnature reserve at the treasured Seven
OL,10,FSisters cliff landscape in East
OL,11,FSussex, and walked part of the King
OL,12,FCharles III England Coast Path on its
OL,13,Flaunch.
OL,15,FThe Seven Sisters National Nature
OL,16,FReserve has become the 13th part of
OL,17,Fthe King's series of nature reserves,
OL,18,Fmarking the halfway point to creating
OL,19,For expanding 25 national nature
OL,20,Freserves by 2028.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
